    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading">
                    <h2 class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading-text">How it wo=
rks</h2>
            </div>
    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__content">
       =20

<p>Users can choose different outfits and accessories for their characters =
to wear and can customise parts of their appearance.</p>



<p>They can then choose from 8 mini-games to play or can create scenes in S=
tudio Mode and become =E2=80=98friends=E2=80=99 with non-player characters =
(NPCs). Some users may upload their Gacha Life stories onto other platforms=
 to share with others.</p>

    </div>
</section>



<section class=3D"anchor-block-item" id=3D"anchor-block-295e705012fdbe4f7aa=
95383ce5c2cb2">
    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading">
                    <h2 class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading-text">Is Gacha =
Life safe for children?</h2>
            </div>
    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__content">
       =20

<p>The Gacha Life app is rated 9+ on the Apple App Store and Everyone on th=
e Google Play Store. Parents should be aware of the chat feature, access to=
 in-app purchases and in-game ads. Ensure you have <a href=3D"https://www.i=
nternetmatters.org/parental-controls/smartphones-and-other-devices/apple-ip=
hone-and-ipad-parental-control-guide/" data-uw-rm-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-origin=
al-href=3D"/parental-controls/smartphones-and-other-devices/apple-iphone-an=
d-ipad-parental-control-guide/">disabled in-app purchases</a> to limit spen=
ding.</p>



<p>In some instances, people raised concerns about <a href=3D"https://www.i=
nternetmatters.org/issues/online-grooming/" data-uw-rm-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-o=
riginal-href=3D"/issues/online-grooming/">strangers requesting underage</a>=
 users to verify their age by sending inappropriate images of themselves.</=
p>



<p>So, it=E2=80=99s important to <a href=3D"https://www.internetmatters.org=
/resources/guide-to-encourage-kids-to-share-their-digital-lives/" data-uw-r=
m-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-original-href=3D"/resources/guide-to-encourage-kids-to=
-share-their-digital-lives/">have conversations</a> with your child about w=
hat they do online and who they talk to. This will help them develop their =
critical thinking of what is and is not acceptable. It=E2=80=99s important =
they understand when to flag something to an appropriate adult should they =
get such requests.</p>



<p><a href=3D"https://lunime.com/privacypolicy/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oreferrer noopener" data-uw-rm-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-original-href=3D"https://=
lunime.com/privacypolicy/" aria-label=3D"Gacha Life=E2=80=99s privacy polic=
y - open in a new tab" data-uw-rm-ext-link=3D"" uw-rm-external-link-id=3D"h=
ttps://lunime.com/privacypolicy/$gachalife=E2=80=99sprivacypolicy">Gacha Li=
fe=E2=80=99s privacy policy</a> encourages parents to be vigilant with thei=
r =E2=80=9Cchildren=E2=80=99s use of e-mail and other online communications=
 and transactional features.=E2=80=9D Parents may request a review and/or r=
emoval of their child=E2=80=99s personal information at any time. They can =
do this by contacting Gacha Life and providing them with the same screen na=
me, password and email address that their child submitted.</p>

    </div>
</section>



<section class=3D"anchor-block-item" id=3D"anchor-block-99b4dd19c5c079ec664=
f1363a4286f77">
    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading">
                    <h2 class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading-text">What is G=
acha Heat?</h2>
            </div>
    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__content">
       =20

<p>Gacha Heat is content generated by users of Gacha Life who upload the co=
ntent on social media platforms like TikTok.</p>



<p>The content is inappropriate and offensive, and it goes beyond stories w=
ithin Gacha Life gameplay. This content may include sexual violence and oth=
er sexual subject matter. It may also feature age-inappropriate relationshi=
ps that normalise abusive behaviours.</p>



<p>It is problematic because of its use of characters and art from the Gach=
a Life mobile video game. Children or young people could view these videos =
on social media apps, thinking it=E2=80=99s appropriate for them when they=
=E2=80=99re not. </p>



<p>Make sure to check what they are watching and <a href=3D"https://www.int=
ernetmatters.org/issues/inappropriate-content/deal-with-it/" data-uw-rm-brl=
=3D"PR" data-uw-original-href=3D"/issues/inappropriate-content/deal-with-it=
/">see how you can support them</a> if they stumble across inappropriate co=
ntent with our advice hub.</p>

    </div>
</section>



<section class=3D"anchor-block-item" id=3D"anchor-block-39ff5cdfbd20f66d90e=
3ca19e4bed790">
    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading">
                    <h2 class=3D"anchor-block-item__heading-text">Ways to k=
eep online gaming safe for children</h2>
            </div>
    <div class=3D"anchor-block-item__content">
       =20

<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>If you want to allow kids to pick apps, but with permission =E2=80=93 <=
a href=3D"https://www.internetmatters.org/parental-controls/smartphones-and=
-other-devices/apples-family-sharing/" data-uw-rm-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-origin=
al-href=3D"/parental-controls/smartphones-and-other-devices/apples-family-s=
haring/">Set up Family Sharing (iPhone)</a> or <a href=3D"https://www.inter=
netmatters.org/parental-controls/smartphones-and-other-devices/google-famil=
y-link/" data-uw-rm-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-original-href=3D"/parental-controls/=
smartphones-and-other-devices/google-family-link/">Family Link (Android)</a=
>.</li>



<li>If you want to prevent access to app stores altogether =E2=80=93 Turn o=
ff the <a href=3D"https://www.internetmatters.org/parental-controls/smartph=
ones-and-other-devices/apple-iphone-and-ipad-parental-control-guide/" data-=
uw-rm-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-original-href=3D"/parental-controls/smartphones-an=
d-other-devices/apple-iphone-and-ipad-parental-control-guide/">App Store in=
 Screen Time (iPhone)</a> or use an <a href=3D"https://www.internetmatters.=
org/parental-controls/smartphones-and-other-devices/android-smartphone/" da=
ta-uw-rm-brl=3D"PR" data-uw-original-href=3D"/parental-controls/smartphones=
-and-other-devices/android-smartphone/">App Lock (Android)</a>.</li>



<li>Talk to your kids about your expectations about what types of apps are =
allowable</li>



<li>Have regular conversations and check-ins about what they are watching o=
r interacting with online.</li>
</ul>

    </div>
</section>
</div>
